&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Consultant Gastroenterologist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This locum consultant appointment is for 3 - 6 months whilst we look to appoint a substantive Consultant to join five enthusiastic and motivated colleagues. The post is for 10 Programmed Activities (PAs) per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Gastroenterology team is cohesive and provides a vast array of services, beyond what would be expected of a District General Hospital. The endoscopy unit is JAG accredited and, as expected, diagnostic and therapeutic gastroscopy, colonoscopy and ERCP services are well established. We have regular GA lists, Endoscopic ultrasound, 24 hour oesophageal pH &amp; manometry and wireless capsule endoscopy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The consultant workforce are supported with a team of Specialist Nurses; 2WTE IBD nurses, 1.3 WTE liver nurses, 2 WTE upper GI/HPB cancer nurses and 1 WTE nutrition nurse. There are 3 Clinical Endoscopists and a further nurse is currently being trained on the HEE programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a rapidly expanding clinical research program with several ongoing academic and commercial studies supported by dedicated research nurses, pharmacists and research coordinators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main duties of the post will include the provision of upper and lower Gastrointestinal Endoscopies, participation in the GI bleed out of hours 1:6 on-call rota, hot week cover for in-patents 1:6 and Gastroenterology outpatient service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are no general medical on call commitments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr A J HughesJob titleClinical LeadTelephone numbersecretaries on 01922 721172 extension 6975Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further information or arrangements for an informal visit may be made by contacting Dr A J Hughes via secretaries on 01922 721172 extension 6975&lt;/p&gt;
